### [Luke Chapter 2](../../../bib/kjv/luk002.htm#001.md)

[Luke 2:1](../../../bib/kjv/luk002.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">luk 2:1</span></span>

world

(Greek, "oikoumenē", means "inhabited earth"). This passage is
noteworthy as defining the usual New Testament use of oikoumene as the
sphere of Roman rule at its greatest extent, that is, of the great
Gentile world-monarchies ([Dan 2:7](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#007).md).
That part of the earth is therefore peculiarly the sphere of prophecy.

